I know what the Marines went through and most others.  To be there was enough and the Recon groups were in a world all to themselves.  If you think it is too horrible to believe, you are right.  I could spew forth true stories on this site that do not need to be told, some still classified.  The horrors of the war have been primarily suppressed.  They recount only the fond memories for their own protection.<br><br>
I hold much back because men like you would call my life a phony because you would believe we could not exist.  Problem is we do.  You can't change facts with words.<br><br>
As often as we have each promised to maintain our civility regression seems to be the norm and not the exception.<br><br>
